      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for iperf3 is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP2.",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Iperf is a tool for active measurements of the maximum achievable bandwidth on IP networks. It supports tuning of various parameters related to timing, protocols, and buffers.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\niPerf3 before 3.17, when used with OpenSSL before 3.2.0 as a server with RSA authentication, allows a timing side channel in RSA decryption operations. This side channel could be sufficient for an attacker to recover credential plaintext. It requires the attacker to send a large number of messages for decryption, as described in \"Everlasting ROBOT: the Marvin Attack\" by Hubert Kario.(CVE-2024-26306)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for iperf3 is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP2.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of low. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Low",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "iperf3",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
